Meeting Minutes – EM Migration Planning Session

Date: [Insert Meeting Date]
Subject: EM Migration – Frabola to New Azure Subscription (3042, East US)
Facilitator: [Your Name]
Attendees: =

1. Purpose

To finalize the migration approach, responsibilities, and next steps for moving the EM application (front-end, Azure SQL, Synapse, and ADLS) from the Frabola subscription to the new Azure subscription 3042 (East US) while ensuring no disruption to itte investigators.

2. Key Discussion Points

Confirmed migration tools and ownership for SQL and Synapse.

Reviewed potential options for ADLS data migration (ADCopy vs ADF).

Discussed dependency on itte for application deployment and testing.

Aligned on requirement for a one-time cut-over with extended maintenance window.

Clarified infrastructure setup (SQL server, clusters, workspace rebuild in new subscription).

3. Finalized Decisions
#	Decision	Responsible Teams
1	Enterprise Data Delivery Pipeline (EDP) confirmed as the migration method for EM SQL and Synapse SQL Pool.	ARE, DAS, DB Engineering
2	itte to install EM v2, perform validation testing with ARE and DAS.	itte, ARE, DAS
3	One-time cut-over after data parity and validation; final sync via EDP and DNS (CNAME) redirect.	App Team, Infra, DB Eng.
4	ADLS migration approach (ADCopy vs ADF) pending renderer meeting next week.	Madan / Renderer / Data Ops
5	New clusters and workspace configurations to be built in subscription 3042; only data moves.	AR&D / Infra
4. Action Items
#	Action Item	Owner(s)	Target Date
1	Execute EDP POC restore benchmark (2–3 TB) to measure timing.	DB Engineering + App Team	This Week
2	Gather POC metrics and finalize Migration Playbook (incl. rollback plan).	ARE + DAS + DB Engineering	Next Week
3	Conduct itte buy-in session for testing and cut-over agreement.	Masood / ami / Bob	Next Week
4	Decide ADLS migration method (ADCopy or ADF).	Renderer / Madan / Data Ops	Next Week
5	Define cut-over maintenance window based on POC timing (target ≤6h).	ARE + App Team + Infra	After POC
6	Update ORAC YAML repo and Priority Task Sheet for akesh team.	ARE / App Team	Ongoing
7	Rebuild Synapse workspace and cluster configurations in new subscription.	AR&D / Infra	In Progress
5. Risks & Dependencies

ADLS migration method pending – could affect timeline.

Restore duration validation required to confirm cut-over window.

itte buy-in and testing timeline critical for scheduling.

6. Next Steps

Complete EDP POC and confirm ADLS approach by next week.

Prepare final cut-over playbook and maintenance window plan.

Align with itte for testing and go-live readiness.

